All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.Shape, java.lang.Cloneable, Shape2D
public class PolarPoint2D
extends Point2D

Define a point with two polar coordinates : rho and theta. Rho is the distance to the origin, and theta is the angle with horizontal, in radians, counted Counter-Clockwise. Internal storage is the same as 'cartesian' point, this class is just a convenient way to create a point when angle and distance are known.
